price tag of perhaps 100,000,000 to 1,000,000,000 dollars.<br>
2. This  space plane has a mass of 15,000 kilograms.<br>
3. It has a 3/1 mass ratio, and a 39,000 pound thrust<br>
nuclear electric arc jet rocket engine with a specific impulse<br>
of 1000 seconds. <br>
4.It has 10,000 kilograms of Loh stored in one 2000 kilogram<br>
titanium metal tank.<br>
5. The whole space plane is made of  Titanium metal.<br>
6.The Loh is pumped by a N-14 gas pressure feed pump.<br>
7.It is powered by a 3,000,000 nuclear fission powered<br>
electric generator that generates 1000 watts of electric power for each pound of its weight.Its weight is 3000<br>
pounds which is 1364 kilograms.<br>
8.The engine has a mass of 800 kilograms .and is made<br>
of Titanium metal. The engine has an LOh cooling jacket<br>
around it. The Loh goes to the cooling jacket, and then <br>
into the arc jet motor. In the  arc jet motor there is a stainless steel anode, and cathode.There is a 3,000,000<br>
watt electric discharge between them which heats  273 grams of Loh to 2500 C per second. It is then expelled<br>
through a delaval nozzle at 10,000 meter/sec.<br>
9.It has delta wings made of Titanium metal. <br>
10. It has a ceramic blanket Heat shield that is designed<br>
to withstand 3000 C on re-entry from leo<br>
11. It lifts off like verticaly like a rocket, and glides <br>
back like a glider.<br>
12.Engine has a mass of 800 kg, and cabin has mass of<br>
800 kg.  <br>
13. It carrys one single person to leo. For more people or<br>
cargo scale it up.<br>
